>>>so im supposing i should update- this weekend was GREAT for the most part. i love my friends, im one damn lucky girl!

doug, robert, and alessandro came to visit erika this weekend from melbourne, and it was really nice seeing ppl from back home. i slept at her place both nights and fun was had by all- we went to a party on friday and got to see erika and ferrah looking beautiful as always, then on sat we went to lunch, dinner at isha's resturant, and to the hooka bar for the night. the boys loved te hooka(who doesnt) and they got to meet britt, my roommate, and the other crazy wonderful ppl that work at the meridian.like RYAN and lil ryan- so many husbands, so little time hah

robert was annoying as hell im sorry but he was.... doug wasnt half as bad as erika made him out to be, i still love im even if he can be immature- pms has that effect on her...
and alessandro is always amazing

still, i cant wait to go home next tusday for my birthday and see everyone and hang out and dance at county line and see harry potter(yes im a dork like that) and see all the friends and family i've been missing for so long.... 

but in the mean time, wednesday, me and alaska are going with my sister and kristen and my mom and jim to see U2 in concert.... should be exciting!

in closing, i love erika and erika, michi and alaska, mags, mollz, britt, rach, alysha, julianna, and bren and jo, and many many many many many other ppl who are very good to me! thank you!

 

hah oh yah i love alex too, we soooooo getting married. well either me or erika, whichever works best. oh, yah, and if you read this, erika(the new one you just met) said you were cute. so you have a chance. be happy!

i've also decided that boys are overrated. and that im going ot stop waiting for that magical combination of me likeing them AND them likeing me cause that never seems to work out. therefore, i'll just wait till someone not half bad wants me and just work with that. at least they'll like me then. who cares what i think??

so lots of shitty things have been happening lately but oh well, its not the end of the world.
i've had to replace my phone 4 times but i think this time it might actually work. had to fix my computer (at best buy- did i mention the 30 minute drive) whereupon they ripped out my hard drive and lost everything i own.. all my quotes, all my music, all my pictures, all my word documents and half written papers. ALWAYS fun stuff. and then it was still acting up (after 7 trips out there that kinda pissed me off!) oh, plus my radio in my car works some days.. but then some days it doesn't- its all kind of random and annoying. 

coupled with class stress i've been having a bad couple of days.

oh yah im changing my major. to what you may ask?? dont know. either advertising or public relations (both mass comm degress) but its all confusing and i have to figure out what i wanna do for the rest of my life. heady stuff, this. what if im wrong? whta if i hate what i do?

who knows. right now im leaning towards working in a publishing company as some sort of pr person/spokesperson. any ideas? anyone? tell me what to do, and save me the trouble.

my birthday is coming up though(NOVEMBER 22), and i cant wait to go home. i want my mommy dammit. and some turkey

Current mood:  tired 


soooo. yah. there was some drama last night. some in my head (cause im an idiot) and some with others who i work with.

to start off with, other than last night (which was still fun but the drama pulled it down a notch) i had a DAMN good weekend for various reasons .. ..  ...... thats right i got some

but last night, i dunno, my head was fucked up. maybe i was just pmsing or something, whatever. almost everyone was pissing me off, hell, i was pissing myself off but i got over that. was supposed to have a kegger at mine but crap happened as usual and it didnt come till late(after i left) 

fortunatly i was with alaska and she kept me sane and not biting anyones head off. we first went to the mclain brothers house which is always fun cause they are CRAZY and they sing alot- erika you missed it!! but after awhile we left (did i mention that im a dumbass? haha not for leaving thats another story.) and we went to dans place and michi, randy, nikki, and julianna were there and we hung out for a bit (god i love julianna i havent seen her in forever) but dan was an ass to nikki so all the females left and on the way out, my boss (suraj who showed up a bit later) told us that we were acting like 12 year olds (which we pretty much were but dan was an ass and deserved it) oh plus, the part where he noticed i had a hickie was GREAT cause i love it when my boss knows what im doing in my spare time! (no incriminating comments please, anyone) 

so we went back to michis and hung for a bit. in the mist of hysterical laughing and dan and suraj calling julianna trying to get us to come back i gave michi a lap dance- she loved it lol- and finally we went back only to be yelled at somemore for leaving but whatever we played asshole(dan's game!) and hung out some more

plus nikki got her revenge hhahaha i didnt think she'd really do it! me and alaska went back to mine and apparently the party was horrible and everyones car got towed so i was glad we didnt stay. 

but tonight is michis bday celebration so im looking forward to it.. will have some good pics too which should last me for awhile

and no school tomarrow SWEET im sleeping in and doing nothing all day. gotta love four day weekends!

i heart college life! despite the drama my friends are amazing and life is good....

um, yah. so i had a crazy ass weekend full of wonderful things. i got a potential boy, so thats always nice. also some some sweet fights and sang many drinking songs and saw michi drunk for the first time, ever... I LOVE MICHI BEAR!!!

got molls to promise to come down to see me for next weekend for about 4 HOURS till she remembered she had better things to do. lame, molls, lame.

sooo, um, i dropped a class today. who needs origins anyways? its totally unnecessary!

and i got married- thats right ladies and gents, alaska is my facebook wife, we're gonna go buy the rings here shortly and it'll be official. im so proud!

thats all i can think of for now, so ta!

blah. maybe i should just go home. or hiberate all day when im not in class with a locked door and blankets over my head and the tv blarring crap i dont wanna watch. or sad girly movies that meke me wanna cry till i remember its just a movie then i really wanna shoot myself for being stupid. wow im being angry for no reason im gonna go to bed now.

i was SUPPOSED to see erika for hr bday after she drove in from melbourne but hse was too hung over, i i think we're going to applebee's after i get out of work tonight o celebrate...

and thats all for now

Pure Nerd
69 % Nerd, 43% Geek, 4% Dork
For The Record:

A Nerd is someone who is passionate about learning/being smart/academia.
A Geek is someone who is passionate about some particular area or subject, often an obscure or difficult one.
A Dork is someone who has difficulty with common social expectations/interactions.
You scored better than half in Nerd, earning you the title of: Pure Nerd.

The times, they are a-changing. It used to be that being exceptionally smart led to being unpopular, which would ultimately lead to picking up all of the traits and tendences associated with the "dork." No-longer. Being smart isn't as socially crippling as it once was, and even more so as you get older: eventually being a Pure Nerd will likely be replaced with the following label: Purely Successful.

now i understand boys can have that effect on a girl, and im happy for them, but when i havent seen that person for 3 weeks, or when i see them everyday (it doesnt matter), would it be alot to ask to hear just one "how are you", even maybe just out of politeness??? is that alot? most ppl say it and dont even mean it. or like when they call you out of the blue and say nothing about you, but do update you on the boy situation and how happy they are. i guess maybe thats the problem, the love between friends that you thought was there really isnt and the only reason your there is because you are. proximity does not a friendship make! anyways im tired of venting im out
